data.analyze.analyze_data(paths, data_dict, display)

Function to analyze data distribution in each of train, test and val dataframe.

Parameters

  • paths – dict of app paths

  • data_dict – dict of train, test, validation pandas data frames

  • display – bool type, display output (images, plots etc.)

data.analyze.plot(paths, data_distribution, key)

Function to plot data distribution in dictionary.

Parameters

  • paths – dict of app paths

  • data_distribution – dict of data distribution in test, train and val data frames

  • key – str key to data_distribution

data.analyze.display_example(paths, data_dict, key)

Function to display 5x5 grid with images and their labels.

Parameters

  • paths – dict of app paths

  • data_dict – dict of train, test, validation pandas data frames

  • key – str key to data_dict

data.analyze.display_values_distribution_values(data_distribution_values)

Function to display quantitative distribution of classes in test, train and validation data frames.

Parameters

data_distribution_values – dict containing distribution details of test, train and validation data frames.

data.analyze.analyze_saved_networks(paths)

Function to analyze saved networks in base app dir. For each network, details .json file is loaded into pandas data frame and displayed. Networks are sorted in data frame descending by FTA (First Test Accuracy).

Parameters

paths – dict of app paths
